    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">Given an integer <var>n</var>, find the product <var>m</var> of the 2 numbers obtained by inverting the <const>first</const> then the <const>second</const> half of the binary representation of <var>n</var>.<br><br><strong>Example:</strong><br><var>n</var> = 8: the binary representation is 1000. the <const>first half inverted</const> is : <const>01</const><strong>00</strong> which is 4, and the <const>second half inverted</const> is <strong>10</strong><const>11</const> which is 11. so the output <var>m</var> is 4*11 = 44.<br><br><strong>Note:</strong><br>if the length of the binary representation of <var>n</var> is odd, <strong>the middle element does not belong to any of the halves</strong>.<br><strong>Example:</strong><br><var>n</var> = 5: the binary representation is 101. the <const>first half inverted</const> is : <const>0</const><strong>01</strong> which is 1, and the <const>second half inverted</const> is <strong>10</strong><const>0</const> which is 4. so the output <var>m</var> is 1*4 = 4.</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\">an integer <var>n</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">an integer <var>m</var> the product of the 2 numbers obtained by inverting the first then the second half of the binary representation of <var>n</var>.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">0 &lt;= <var>n</var> &lt;= 1000</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement